  <p>
    I'm currently the AI SME for the DEVCOM AvMC Software Assurance team. Day to day, I design and build AI-augmented tooling for Army aviation and missile software-assurance programs. That work covers LLM and RAG pipelines over CWE and CVE corpora, Code Property Graph (CPG) and AST-based static analysis, knowledge graphs, assurance dashboards, federated artifact-management research, and the papers and briefs that come out of all of it.
  </p>

  <p>
    Earlier in my COLSA tenure I led a 40+ engineer organization delivering containerized ML platforms for real-time signal characterization and anomaly detection.
  </p>

  <p>
    My PhD research at Purdue is on what happens to frontier LLMs when they're cut off from the live internet. How they drift. How to measure that drift. How to keep them reliable when they're running in offline or air-gapped environments.
  </p>

  <p>
    The combination on this profile is unusual. AI depth, plus real security credentials (CISSP, B.S. Information Assurance, 11 years in cleared environments), plus robotics and autonomous-systems work (TARDEC ground vehicles, UAV swarming, Georgia Tech's Computational Perception & Robotics specialization). Most AI engineers don't have the security background. Most security engineers don't ship LLMs.
  </p>

  <p>
    Open to senior IC, Engineering Manager, or Director roles at fully remote companies. AI labs, AI security, AI-native scaleups, robotics, regulated-industry AI teams.
  </p>

